==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inspirit
<hw>In*spir"it</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Inspirited</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Inspiriting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To infuse new life or spirit
into; to animate; to encourage; to invigorate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The courage of Agamemnon is <qex>inspirited</qex> by the love of
empire and ambition.</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To enliven; invigorate; exhilarate; animate;
cheer; encourage; inspire.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inspissate</ent>⟦br⟧
